{
  "text": "A few studies have addressed the issue of symmetry of aberrations between the right and left eyes of the patients, after corneal laser refractive surgery [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Independently developed ray-tracing programs [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] have been used to determine the functional optical zone (FOZ) after the refractive surgery. A direct approach to measure FOZ after refractive surgery has been proposed by manually determining the transition region between the treated and untreated areas from corneal topography maps [CITATION_5] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "6475930",
